Class Order

java.lang.Object
marketplace.Objects.Order
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
BuyOrderHistory, SellOrder
public class Order
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
Order class, parent for buy and sell orders. Holds information about an asset, it's connected organisation and other details.
See Also:
OrderHandler, Serialized Form

    • Order

      public Order​(java.lang.String orderID, java.lang.String userID, java.lang.String assetName, int quantity, java.math.BigDecimal price, java.sql.Timestamp orderDate)
      Constructor for Order object.
      Parameters:
      orderID - is the unique identifier for each order, so it can be found in the database.
      userID - is the userID of the user who placed the sell or buy order.
      assetName - is the name of the asset being either sold or bought.
      quantity - is the quantity of the asset being sold or bought in whole numbers.
      price - is the price that the orders are active for or have been fullfilled with.
      orderDate - is the data time of the order.
